This paper deals with a problem related to maintaining connectivity in a dynamic graph, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper proposes a new data structure that improves the worst-case update time for the problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
